The paper proposes a new architecture for processing clinical time-series data using Sequence Transformer Networks, which is a type of neural network. The paper discusses the advantages of this approach over other methods, such as dynamic time warping, for identifying and accounting for invariances in the data. The paper also evaluates the proposed approach on the task of predicting in-hospital mortality. Given these factors, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and computational linguistics (cs.CL).
